Monday 6 April 2026

Parents to Woodford, London

Drive back to Woodford, London.

Because it is a bank holiday Monday, an early departure is the safest move to reduce traffic risk. That is a planning recommendation rather than a live traffic forecast.

Booking Priorities

Book in this order:
	1.	Hotel for Thu 2 Apr and Fri 3 Apr
	2.	Friday lunch or dinner reservation, depending on where you most care about eating
	3.	Saturday if you want any fixed Leamington lunch stop
	4.	Lincoln tickets once your hotel is secured
	5.	Belvoir only if you decide to swap it in, which I do not recommend for this exact version

Best restaurant strategy

For this trip shape, I would do:
	•	Thu 2 Apr dinner: The Finch’s Arms or Hitchen’s Barn
	•	Fri 3 Apr lunch: The Bronze Pig in Lincoln
	•	Fri 3 Apr dinner: relaxed dinner back in Hambleton, unless you stay at Hambleton Hall and dine there

This gives you one easy dinner, one strong city lunch, and one quiet countryside evening.

Budget Range

Best-fit version with The Finch’s Arms

Because I could not verify a live direct room rate from the hotel’s own booking engine in search results, this budget is partly estimated.
	•	Hotel: variable, likely moderate country-inn pricing with Easter uplift
	•	Lincoln Cathedral + Lincoln Castle: paid tickets for both
	•	Dining: one stronger meal plus one easier dinner
	•	Leamington: discretionary shopping spend on top

A realistic trip envelope for two, excluding shopping, is:
	•	Moderate version: roughly £650–£1,050
	•	Premium version: roughly £1,050–£1,600+

The range moves mainly with hotel choice and how ambitious Friday dining becomes. Hambleton Hall pushes the trip into a clearly higher spend category because its 2026 rates are explicitly published at a premium level and Easter exclusions remove the cheaper seasonal rates.  ￼

Final Recommendation

This is the cleanest version of your trip:
	•	Wed 1 Apr: Woodford, London to parents
	•	Thu 2 Apr: parents to Hambleton / Oakham, overnight
	•	Fri 3 Apr: Lincoln cathedral-and-castle day, second overnight
	•	Sat 4 Apr: return west via Leamington Spa shopping, then back to parents
	•	Sun 5 Apr: Easter lunch
	•	Mon 6 Apr: home to Woodford, London

It has the right rhythm:
	•	family
	•	escape
	•	proper heritage day
	•	useful soft-return day
	•	family again

